<subSubSection pageId="149" pageNumber="547" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="149.[121,1328,1557,2261]" pageId="149" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[123,477,2069,2102]" pageId="149" pageNumber="547">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List. Sclater’s Mouse Shrew seems to be threatened by human development, overgrazing, and general habitat destruction over its small distribution. The species is considered fairly common within its restricted range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
